				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/c-dives" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2375337); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2375337&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183424" alt="C-Dives" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2375337)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/c-dives" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2375337); return false;" >C-Dives</a></span> <span class="odate time_1574473855 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Nov 2019 01:50</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4429675">
									

<blockquote>
<p>All images used in the article itself are in the public domain.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Uh, actually, there are two exceptions. And <em>at least</em> one of them is not compliant with CC-BY-SA 3.0.</p>
<ul>
<li>Locus-248-J is <span style="text-decoration: underline;">CC BY-SA 4.0</span> (&quot;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Pub,_Interior.jpg">File:Pub, Interior.jpg</a>&quot;, posted by Serial Number 54129). I still firmly believe all CC 4.0 images should be non-compliant with this site (as it's under CC 3.0), but I'm not here to discuss about this problem.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Bottle cap used in &quot;Photoshopped&quot; image is from Pexels, which switched its license from CC0 to &quot;<a href="https://www.pexels.com/photo-license/">Pexels License</a>&quot; since <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:Pexels-Cc-zero">2018/07/05</a>. This license has prohibited to &quot;redistribute or sell the photos on other stock photo or wallpaper platforms&quot;— this is not compatible with CC BY-SA 3.0, which has allowed image redistribution and commercial use. Apparently the author (Brett Jordan) posted this image on 2019/07/25, so it's clearly under Pexels License.</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
					
